data.enText: a person who has or owns the thing mentioned

data.chText: 目前的世界纪录保持者
data.enText: the current holder of the world record
the holder of a French passport
a thing that holds the object mentioned

tr: the person who is in possession of a check or note or bond or document of title that is endorsed to him or to whoever holds it
example: the bond was marked `payable to bearer'
she holds a United States passport

value.def: A holder is someone who owns or has something.

example.ex: This season the club has had 73,500 season-ticket holders.
example.tran: 本赛季该俱乐部已经有73,500名持有季票的观众。

example.ex: ...Peter Koech, the record holder in the 3,000 metres steeplechase.
example.tran: 3,000米障碍赛跑的纪录保持者彼得·克奇

example.ex: ...the holders of the European Football Championship.
example.tran: 拥有欧洲足球锦标赛冠军称号的球队

value.def: A holder is a container in which you put an object, usually in order to protect it or to keep it in place.
